#: /home/ruscher/Documentos/Git/_REFIZ/bigcam/usr/share/biglinux/bigcam/ui/about_dialog.py:39
msgid ""
"The universal webcam control center for Linux.\n"
"\n"
"BigCam was born as a small shell script so that Rafael Ruscher could use his Canon Rebel T3 as a webcam during live streams about BigLinux. That humble hack, written by Rafael and Barnabé di Kartola, evolved from a Bash bridge between gPhoto2 and FFmpeg into a full GTK4/Adwaita application with live preview, multi-backend camera support (V4L2, gPhoto2, libcamera, PipeWire, IP cameras, smartphones), real-time OpenCV effects, virtual camera output, photo and video capture, and 29 languages."
msgstr ""
"Univerzálne centrum ovládania webkamery pre Linux.\n"
"\n"
"BigCam vznikol ako malý shell skript, aby Rafael Ruscher mohol použiť svoj Canon Rebel T3 ako webkameru počas živých prenosov o BigLinux. Tento skromný hack, ktorý napísali Rafael a Barnabé di Kartola, sa vyvinul z Bash mosta medzi gPhoto2 a FFmpeg do plnohodnotnej aplikácie GTK4/Adwaita s náhľadom naživo, podporou viacerých backendov kamier (V4L2, gPhoto2, libcamera, PipeWire, IP kamery, smartfóny), efektmi OpenCV v reálnom čase, výstupom virtuálnej kamery, zachytávaním fotografií a videí a 29 jazykmi."

